&lt;p>Let us say two variables A &amp;amp; B. Initially both are equal to 4.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>A&lt;em>B = 16 &lt;br>
4&lt;/em>4 = 16 &lt;br>
8&lt;em>2 = 16 &lt;br>
16&lt;/em>1=16 &lt;br>
160*.1=16 &lt;br>
16,000,000,00*.000,000,01=16&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Observation:&lt;/strong> &lt;br>
In the final step, the first part is extraordinarily large. &lt;br>
